<br>
The trick takes advantage of a little known quirk of aggro rules. There are two aggro radii to be considered when aggroing a mob. The first is your own radius: the mob will aggro on you because he hates you. The second is a mobs &quot;help&quot; radius, whereby a mob that is chasing you will aggro his friends against you as well.<br>
<br>
If you or a mob are in combat, your respective aggro radii become larger. If you do anything offensive to a mob when pulling it, like hitting it or casting a spell on it, its &quot;help&quot; radius will become significantly larger. That's why you have more success pulling single fish in Kedge by swimming into their range, rather than by casting on them. Mobs that are pulled because they are coming to &quot;help&quot;, but have not actually aggroed on <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> you</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, have a very small aggro radius indeed, and this is what you are taking advantage of.<br>
<br>
In the frenzied ghoul's room, you can pull each side ghoul alone by fighting another ghoul in their room. You hug the wall and very carefully &quot;push&quot; your enemy frog into the BT's aggro range, without getting the BT into your own aggro range. This requires some careful jockeying and taking advantage of pathing, which is why I suspect it can't be done with a pet. The side ghoul will come to help his friend, but this one's aggro radius will be very small until he actually sees and engages you, so he doesn't bring the center ghoul.<br>
<br>
That's how we would break frenzied when we didn't have the right classes for breaking the room properly. This info may be useful to you, who knows. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 40th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showPrevMessage?topicID=117.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showNextMessage?topicID=117.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=117.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.threadControl?topicID=117.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=117.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=117.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option